article.headline: Dayton 40, Austin Peay 0
article.story:
CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. (AP) -- Jason Resch kicked four field goals --
his longest 38 yards -- Saturday to help Dayton shut out Austin Peay
40-0.

Resch's 38-yarder came early in the first quarter. In the second
quarter, he kicked one for 25 yards with 7:56 to go before the
half. And in the third quarter, he made field goals from 33 and 23
yards.

The Flyers (3-1) had a total of 253 yards rushing, compared to
34 for the Governors (0-4). Dayton also had 147 yards passing,
where Austin Peay had a total of 89.

Dayton quarterback Brandon Staley was 12 of 16 for 123 yards.
Ron Wrobleski led all Dayton receivers with 99 yards.
